Reasoning: The paper deals with algebraic methods applied to formal languages and automata, which are topics typically studied in theoretical computer science. The use of Hilbert's Basis Theorem and the study of decidability of equivalence problems suggest a focus on logic and computability, placing the paper in the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science) categories. The mention of formal languages and transducers also suggests a connection to cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The study of register automata and forests suggests a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
